Kingboard Chemical Agrees to HK$4.8 Billion Loan Facility

-- B y   W e n d y   L e u n g
-- 
2011-04-03T11:26:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/kingboard-chemical-agrees-to-hk-4-8-billion-loan-facility.html
Kingboard Chemical Holdings Ltd. (148) , a
Hong Kong-based maker of laminates and industrial materials,
agreed a HK$4.8 billion ($617 million) loan facility from banks.  The five-year syndicated loan was “fully underwritten” by
three arrangers and bookrunners, including Citigroup Global
Markets Asia Ltd., HSBC Holdings Plc and  Standard Chartered Plc (STAN) ,
Kingboard said in a faxed statement today.  The company will use the loan to refinance existing debt
and finance “general corporate requirements”, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Leung in  Hong Kong  at 
